body:
@pjfanning That's something to consider too I suppose, although its actually usage should be less problematic as lookup maps are bound to individual `ObjectMapper`s and there are no static singletons.

Having said that.... I am starting to think that maybe `AnnotationIntrospector` static instance really should go too. It being stateful makes that a bad idea.
So perhaps I'll do both (1) and (2).
